   <conbody>
      <conbodydiv class="- topic/bodydiv concept/conbodydiv ">
         <section class="- topic/section ">
            <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
               <hazardstatement conref="../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/separate_redundant_units"
                                class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
                  <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                     <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
                     <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
                  </messagepanel>
               </hazardstatement>
               <p class="- topic/p ">Systems with multiple units can have an output
couple switch to control the load sharing between the units.</p>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph class="- topic/ph ">Redundant systems use a normally closed (NC) output couple switch
to share the load by default.</ph>
                  <ph otherprops="typeD" class="- topic/ph "> Dual systems
use a normally open (NO) output couple switch to supply individual
loads by default.</ph>
               </p>
               <p class="- topic/p ">NO and NC output couple switches are
operated in the same way.</p>
            </sectiondiv>
         </section>
         <section class="- topic/section ">
            <title class="- topic/title ">How to Open the Output Couple Switch</title>
            <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">To open the output couple switch and separate the outputs:</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check that:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">The system is running in <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
                                 <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph> (with all units active).</p>
                           </li>
                           <li class="- topic/li ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">No alarms are pending on any unit.</p>
                           </li>
                        </ol>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Open the output couple switch.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
               <p class="- topic/p ">The system output is now separated and each unit is supplying
its own load.</p>
            </sectiondiv>
         </section>
      </conbodydiv>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">How to Close the Output Couple Switch</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">To
close the output couple switch and connect the outputs:</p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The units are all running in <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal
operation</ph>
                           <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph> (individually).</p>
                     </li>
                     <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The bypass mains and static switch EN are
available for all units and within tolerance (check status on the
mimic diagram).</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">No alarms are pending.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ol>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch over <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u> to static bypass
operation:<ol conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Switch-to-bypass"
                      class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li "/>
                  </ol>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Follow the same procedure and switch over <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> to bypass operation.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> on <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">both
units</u> show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the external load connection is closed.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Close the output couple switch.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch over <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit1</u> to normal operation:<ol conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Switch-to-normal"
                      class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li "/>
                  </ol>
               </p>
               <note class="- topic/note ">The load will be supplied by the bypass until all units
in the system have been switched back to normal operation.</note>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Follow the same procedure and switch over <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">unit2</u> to normal operation.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> on <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">both
units</u> show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the system operates correctly and no alarms are present.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The system is now in redundant/parallel operation with all
units supplying an equal share of the load.</p>
      </section>
